note.p:
Order to the commissioners of the muster for Norfolk (England)
                        to send an account of their troops. Signed by twelve members of
                        the privy council of Elizabeth I, Queen of England:
                            John Whitgift (then Archbishop of
                        Canterbury); Sir Thomas Egerton; Thomas
                            Sackville, Earl of Dorset (then Baron Buckhurst);
                            Charles Howard, Earl of Nottingham;
                            Gilbert Talbot, Earl of Shrewsbury;
                            Edward Somerset, Earl of Worcester;
                            William Knollys, Earl of Banbury;
                            John Stanhope; Robert Cecil,
                            Earl of Salisbury; J. Fortescu;
                            Sir John Popham; and Sir John
                            Herbert.

Fragment of a letter signed jointly by Francis Bacon (1561-1626);
                            Sir Thomas Egerton (then Baron
                        Ellesmere); Fulke Greville, Baron Brooke; Sir
                            Julius Caesar; Edward Somerset, Earl of Worcester;
                        and George Carew, Earl of Totnes.

Order to the commissioners of the loans for the city of Coventry
                            (England). Signed by fifteen members of the privy council of
                            Charles I, King of England, including
                            William Herbert, 3rd Earl of Pembroke;
                            Philip Herbert, Earl of Pembroke (then
                        Earl of Montgomery); Theophilus Howard, Earl of Suffolk;
                            William Cecil, Earl of Salisbury;
                            William Cecil, Earl of Exeter;
                            John Egerton, Earl of Bridgewater;
                            Oliver St. John, Viscount Grandison of Limerick;
                            Edward Conway, Viscount Conway of Conway Castle;
                            Dudley Carleton, 1st Viscount Dorchester;
                            Sir Thomas Edmondes; Sir John
                            Suckling; Sir John Coke; Sir
                            Julius Caesar; and others.

did.unittitle:
Harden, [John William, b. ca. 1810?] Requisition of Mr. Rudall;
                            observations of Mr. Harden in reply : autograph manuscript, [no
                        place] 1844 July 10.

note.p:
Discusses his close acquaintance with Thomas Sheridan;
                        mentions Samuel Johnson and David
                            Garrick.

Concerning a membership election for the Literary Club;
                        opposes James Boswell's candidates. With
                        cover.
